org.knime.base.node.mine.util

Class PredictorHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.base.node.mine.util.PredictorHelper

  • public class PredictorHelper
extends Object
    Helper class to create predictor output table specification with a common naming scheme.

    The prediction column should have the following form: Prediction (TrainingColumn) (only default) and P (TrainingColumn=Value) with possible suffix for the probability columns.

    Since:
    2.9
    Author:
    Gabor Bakos

        public DialogComponentString addPredictionColumn(DefaultNodeSettingsPane dialog,
                                                 SettingsModelString predictionColumn,
                                                 SettingsModelBoolean changePredictionColName)
        Adds the prediction column name to the dialog. After that horizontal placement is set.
        Please make sure to initialize the changePredictionColName model properly or fire the model state change listeners.
        Parameters:
        dialog - A DefaultNodeSettingsPane.
        predictionColumn - The SettingsModelString for the custom prediction column.
        changePredictionColName - The SettingsModelBoolean for overriding the prediction column.
        Returns:
        The created DialogComponentString, although the dialog will also contain a checkbox to enable/disable the custom column name.

      • checkedComputePredictionColumnName

        public String checkedComputePredictionColumnName(String predictionColumn,
                                                 boolean shouldOverride,
                                                 String trainingColumnName)
                                          throws InvalidSettingsException
        Checks whether the prediction column name would be empty or not.
        Parameters:
        predictionColumn - The overridden value for the prediction column name.
        shouldOverride - Use the overridden value (true), or the computed (false)?
        trainingColumnName - The name of the column used to train the model.
        Returns:
        The custom name if the model is enabled, else the pattern specified by computePredictionDefault(String).
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Wrong prediction column name.
        Since:
        2.12
        See Also:
        computePredictionDefault(String), computePredictionColumnName(String, boolean, String)

      • createOutTableSpec

        public DataTableSpec createOutTableSpec(PortObjectSpec dataSpec,
                                        PortObjectSpec modelSpec,
                                        boolean addProbs,
                                        String predictionCol,
                                        boolean shouldOverride,
                                        String suffix)
                                 throws InvalidSettingsException
        Computes the output table's specifaction based on common node settings.
        Parameters:
        dataSpec - The input table DataColumnSpec.
        modelSpec - The model PMMLPortObjectSpec.
        addProbs - Add the probability columns?
        predictionCol - Custom name of the prediction column.
        shouldOverride - Should we use that name?
        suffix - Suffix for probability columns.
        Returns:
        The output table DataTableSpec.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Invalid settings for the prediction column name.
